pressure
The Railway deployment configuration is competent for basic operation. The railway.toml
configures port 8080, GitHub the Dockerfile uses a multi-stage build (build stage compiles
OpenClaw from source, runtime stage uses lean Debian with tini ), Railway and the
volume mount at /data persists state across redeploys.
Memory is the critical infrastructure bottleneck. The OpenClaw gateway requires
approximately 530-550MB (450MB V8 heap + 80-100MB runtime overhead) just to idle,
before conversation context accumulation. GitHub The Railway Hobby plan provides only
512MB Railway — below the minimum. The README warns about Reached heap limit
